// Secrets.xcconfig.example  —  BRING-YOUR-OWN-KEY template (NO real secrets live here)
// =====================================================================================
// This is a TEMPLATE. It contains ZERO real keys. The recommended path for this app is
// the in-app "paste your key -> Keychain" flow (see Keys/), which needs NO build-config
// plumbing at all. This xcconfig route is an OPTIONAL local-dev convenience.
//
// Copy it to a GITIGNORED real file and paste YOUR OWN value:
//     cp Config/Secrets.xcconfig.example Config/Secrets.xcconfig
//
// GOTCHA: xcconfig build settings are NOT visible to Swift at runtime by themselves.
// To read one in code, surface it through the generated Info.plist with
//     INFOPLIST_KEY_OPENAI_API_KEY = $(OPENAI_API_KEY)
// then read via Bundle.main.object(forInfoDictionaryKey: "OPENAI_API_KEY").
// The Keychain flow avoids this plumbing entirely and is preferred for an OSS app.
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

// Defaults are intentionally EMPTY so a fresh clone (no Secrets.xcconfig) still compiles.
OPENAI_API_KEY =
